                "actions": {
                    "value": 2
                },
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p>The accursed forge-spurned breathes a cloud of stinging soot, ash, and glowing embers. This can affect either a 30-foot cone or a 20-foot burst centered on the accursed forge-spurned and persists for 1d4 rounds. Creatures that move into or start their turn in the area take [[/r 12d6 # fire damage]] fire damage (<span data-pf2-check=\"reflex\" data-pf2-dc=\"36\" data-pf2-traits=\"divine,evocation,fire,damaging-effect\" data-pf2-label=\"Forge Breath DC\" data-pf2-show-dc=\"gm\">basic Reflex</span> save). A creature that fails its save is also blinded for 1 minute. Creatures within the cloud are concealed, though not from the accursed forge-spurned. The accursed forge-spurned can't use Forge Breath again until it has used Inflate Bellows.</p>"
                },
